# Microservice

## Purpose

- Host specialized operations for database key rotation and re-encryption
- Provide migrate endpoints (routes/migrate.get.ts, migrate.post.ts) invoked by CronJob or admin workflows
- Share Prisma schema subset sufficient for operations on encrypted models

## Structure

- server.ts — Nitro/H3 entrypoint
- routes/ — migrate and test endpoints
- clients/ — prismaClient.ts, redisClient.ts (aligned with app behavior)
- lib/bull.ts — BullMQ setup utilities
- prisma/ — schema.prisma, migrations, reencrypt/ generated
- scripts/k8s-rotate-db-key.sh — in-cluster script used by runner-keyrotate image

## Docker targets

- Default runner (production) — pnpm start (prestart runs migrate-with-retry.js)
- runner-keyrotate — adds kubectl/jq; used only for the staging CronJob

## Deployment

- Built/pushed in PR and main workflows (gcr.io/.../dineros-microservice:<tag>)
- Deployed alongside main app using .deploy/dineros.template.yaml; service on port 3050
- ENV taken from K8s secrets; INTERNAL_API_TOKEN propagated for secure internal calls

